        <content type="html"><![CDATA[
            <p>How do the books of the KJV Bible compare to each other word for word?  Are Old Testament books more similar to other Old Testament books?  Same for the New Testament?  What about the Greek (Nestle-Aland 26th/27th edition) translation of the New Testament?</p>

<p>Naturally, I wrote a little perl program of the classic <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Natural-language_processing">NLP</a> measure to tell me: <a href="https://github.com/ology/Lex/blob/master/cosine-similarity">cosine-similarity</a>.  It is not the most efficient but it works perfectly!</p>

